    <note>Yang(2) Fei [10564] Lineage history in XTS, 71b.46b. Hu Quan's ancestry identifies Lu [10562] as a 6th generation descendant of Chengxiu, when chronological logic would make him a 6th generation ancestor of Fei and son of Chengxiu [4038] (33rd generation descendant of Zhen(2) [12357] [genealogical tables would make a 23rd generation descendant, not an uncommon copying error]). Lu's son, Xiang [12934], is identified as a 8th generation ancestor of Fei, whereas chronological logic and placement in the inscription would make him a great great grandfather. See also documentation for Yang(2) Daya [2029]. Fei was clearly a wealthy member of the local gentry. His wife was born Luo and his lineage is probably related to that of Yang(2) Tong [13187] (q.v.). Hu Quan, WJ, 25.22a-23b. CBD, 4, 3110-2.</note>
